caption: @haadthai  Wow ❤️ Great time at Haad Thai in DC the location on 11th street, oh and by the way this location is very cool because it is inside of a historic building that once was a Greyhound Bus Terminal. I was showed the wall of photos and history by the very welcoming and knowledgeable manager on duty. Overall I had a really great time 🤗🤩😁all of the food was great and I would ask that you try the 👉 Calamari , the 👉 Steamed dumplings and if you like Cocktails 🍸 then take a chance on the Volcano 🌋 drink and the Mai Tai. 😊 Thankyou ❤ for taking the time to read my review and please feel free to click on the follow button on my profile and I will also follow back, by the way I also do some reviews on Instagram so feel free to follow my page there as well and thanks for the support @chefkamalc😀 😊 🙌 ❤

My wife and I planned a quiet weekend in DC, only to get stuck in sudden traffic; Biden had won the electoral vote. We tried making our way back to our hotel but streets had been blocked by the police. All the rerouting confused my Garmin and we were already getting hangry at each other😄 Luckily a car pulled out of a parking space and I quickly sidled up to the curb. There were a couple of other restaurants along the street, but we decided to go to the emptiest one; with covid rising again and all. So glad we ended up in Haad Thai!👍  Hands down, the most authentic Thai food I’ve tasted in a while. I ordered the Tom Yum and it was delightful. It was a perfect balance of sour, sweet, spicy soup, complemented by mushrooms, tomatoes, and shrimp. You can taste it from the aroma alone. A good whiff gives you that citrusy sensation from the lemongrass and galangal. The lime instantly bounces on your tongue at first taste of the soup. It’s like a sigh of relief after a long drive into DC. It was small serving however, next time I’ll ask if they have meal portions.  The Pad Thai is actually street food in Thailand, but it is divine. The merry mix up of ingredients is brought together by the perfect blend of tamarind juice and palm sugar, which make up the base sauce. Each forkful of noodles is chewy goodness in your mouth. This basic dish alone is worth coming back to.  We also had the lunch special which was a pumpkin curry with pork. They can prepare it with your protein of choice. They can also spice it up to your taste. It’s a straight up curry dish, but the cubes of pumpkin adds a yummy level to the dish. I understand that most Americans know pumpkin as a pie ingredient, but Asians have it as vegetable. Think of it as a sweet potato in a savory recipe. Like a great meal, all flavors from the soup, to the noodles, to the last dollop of curry sauce on the rice all melded together for a great, historic day in DC!

Fresh made and delivered daily, I will dream about those wide, perfectly chewy noodles. I hope this place survives the pandemic so we can visit one day again.

Had a hankering for Thai food and decided to check out Haad Thai based on the promising reviews (and close proximity to my hotel). Was surprised that the restaurant was full at 1 p.m. on a Thursday, a good sign! Atmosphere: Cozy with a pleasant, tropical motif (painted on the walls was a beachy, paradise-like background) and tiny lights hung from the ceiling. Customer service: Everyone was very friendly, polite and served with a smile. Food: I ordered the house salad with the peanut dressing. It was served to me immediately, which typically is a bit off-putting since I'm never sure how long it has been sitting in the cooler; however, the salad was crisp, cool, refreshing and very delicious! Loved the dressing. I ordered the Panang Duck based on the recommendation of my server when I asked her which duck dish was 'the best'. And it was very good. I was a bit disappointed at the portion size when it first arrived, but later realized how filling it was. Served with rice, four pieces of broccoli and a few slices of duck. I wasn't impressed with how fatty the outside ring of the duck was. In the past, the duck I've eaten at Thai restaurants has had a very crisp skin; albeit, this was delicious!  I would certainly recommend and will come back on my next visit.
